quran[96]{c,v,t}:
  56,1,When the Inevitable Event comes to pass
  56,2,There is no denying that it will come
  56,3,"Abasing some, exalting others"
  56,4,When the earth shall be shaken to its foundations
  56,5,And the mountains shall be crumbled
  56,6,So that they shall be as scattered dust
  56,7,And you shall be sorted into three classes
  56,8,First the companions of the right hand - what will be the companions of the right hand
  56,9,And then the companions of the left hand - what will be the companions of the left hand
  56,10,And those foremost (in faith) will be the foremost (in the Hereafter)
  56,11,These are they who are drawn nigh (to Allah)
  56,12,In the Gardens of Bliss
  56,13,A multitude of those of old
  56,14,And a few of those of later times
  56,15,On thrones decorated
  56,16,"Reclining on them, facing one another"
  56,17,Round about them shall serve youths of permanent freshness (immortal or never altering in age)
  56,18,With goblets and ewers and a cup filled from a pure fountain
  56,19,"They shall not suffer with headache thereby, nor shall they get intoxicated (or exhausted)"
  56,20,And fruits such as they choose
  56,21,And the flesh of fowl and any as they desire
  56,22,"And pure, beautiful companions"
  56,23,The like of the well-preserved pearls
  56,24,A reward for what they used to do
  56,25,They shall not hear therein vain or sinful discourse
  56,26,"Except the saying, \"Peace! Peace"
  56,27,And the companions of the right hand; what of the companions of the Right Hand
  56,28,Amid thornless Lote-trees
  56,29,And tall trees with clusters of flowers (or fruits) one above another
  56,30,And spreading shade
  56,31,And water flowing constantly
  56,32,And abundant fruit
  56,33,Neither intercepted nor forbidden
  56,34,And exalted thrones
  56,35,Surely We have created them into a new creation
  56,36,And made them virgins pure
  56,37,"Loving friends, equals in age"
  56,38,For the sake of the companions of the right hand
  56,39,A multitude of those of old
  56,40,And a multitude of those of later times
  56,41,And those of the left hand; what of those of the Left Hand
  56,42,In hot wind and boiling water
  56,43,And the shade of black smoke
  56,44,Neither cool nor honourable
  56,45,Surely they were before this made to live in ease and plenty
  56,46,And they persisted in the great violation (or great sin)
  56,47,"And they used to say, \"What! When we die and have become dust and bones, shall we then indeed be raised"
  56,48,Or our fathers of yore
  56,49,"Say, \"The first and the last"
  56,50,Shall most surely be gathered together for the appointed hour of a known day
  56,51,"Then shall you, O you who err and call it a lie"
  56,52,Most surely eat of a tree of Zaqqum
  56,53,And fill your bellies therewith
  56,54,Then drink over it boiling water
  56,55,And drink as drinks the thirsty camel
  56,56,This is their entertainment on the Day of Requital
  56,57,"We have created you, why do you not then assent"
  56,58,Have you considered the seed (or what you emit)
  56,59,Is it you that create it or are We the creators
  56,60,We have ordained death among you and We are not to be frustrated
  56,61,That We may transfigure you and make you grow into what you know not
  56,62,"And certainly you know the first growth, why do you not then reflect"
  56,63,Have you considered what you sow
  56,64,"Is it you that cause it to grow, or are We the cause"
  56,65,"If We willed, We could crumble it to powder, then would you lament"
  56,66,Surely we are burdened with debt
  56,67,Nay! We are deprived
  56,68,Have you considered the water which you drink
  56,69,"Is it you that send it down from the clouds, or are We the senders"
  56,70,"If We willed, We could have made it salty; why do you not then give thanks"
  56,71,Have you considered the fire which you strike
  56,72,"Is it you that produce the trees for it, or are We the producers"
  56,73,We have made it a reminder and a convenience for the dwellers of the deserts
  56,74,"Therefore, glorify the name of your Lord, the Supreme"
  56,75,But nay! I swear by the setting (or falling or fading) of stars
  56,76,And most surely it is a very great oath if you only knew
  56,77,Most surely it is an honoured Quran
  56,78,In a book that is protected
  56,79,None shall touch it save the purified ones
  56,80,A revelation by the Lord of the worlds
  56,81,Do you then hold this announcement in contempt
  56,82,And make denial of it your means of subsistence
  56,83,Why then do you not (intervene) when the soul comes up to the throat (of a dying person)
  56,84,And you the while look on
  56,85,"And We are nearer to it (the soul) than you, but you see not"
  56,86,"Then why, if you are not under Our authority"
  56,87,"Force back (the soul), if you are truthful (about your independence)"
  56,88,Then if he is one of those Near to Allah
  56,89,(There is for him) Satisfaction and Bounty and a Garden of Bliss
  56,90,And if he is one of those on the Right Hand
  56,91,"Then (the salutation) \"Peace to you\" from the companions of the Right Hand"
  56,92,"And if he is one of the rejecters, the erring ones"
  56,93,He shall have an entertainment of boiling water
  56,94,And burning in Hell
  56,95,Most surely this is a certain truth (or the Truth of Certainty)
  56,96,"Therefore glorify the name of your Lord, the Supreme"